{"id":"h_mr5k39hu_ww0o","text":"When the user says \"ascii galaxy\" or \"/galaxy\" they mean the pi TUI extension ~/.pi/agent/extensions/void-blackhole.ts, not the ~/Developer/galaxy website (which is the lensed-blackhole personal site).","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"correction","created":"2026-07-03T23:20:08.658Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-03T23:20:08.658Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5kbx4v_1iwy","text":"In pi, the header (ctx.ui.setHeader) is the first element of the scrolling transcript and scrolls off-screen once messages arrive; for a persistently-visible element use ctx.ui.setWidget (sticky above/below editor), setFooter, or setStatus instead.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-03T23:26:52.542Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-03T23:26:52.542Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
